<HEAD>Record Number of Tourists Visit Britain in 1987</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A record 15.4 million foreign tourists visited <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> last year, including many more Japanese, Europeans and North Americans, the <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tourist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Authority </ORGANIZATION> said. The figure marked an 11 percent increase from 1986, and the visitors spent $ 10.4 billion, the authority said Thursday. The authority said 1987 visits by Japanese increased 45 percent from 1986 while those by Greeks and Italians increased 38 percent. North American tourists in 1987 increased by 19 percent from the year before, said the government-funded authority. The tourist authority said <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> was fifth in tourism earnings for a second consecutive year last year, after the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Spain </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>.
