<TEXT>
 A mild protest or two is not out of the ordinary at Sen. <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>'s campaign appearances. Allegations that the senator pulled strings to get into the National Guard during the Vietnam War have prompted signs like `` War Wimp'' and `` Sissy Rich Boy'' to pop up here and there. But reporters who follow the <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> vice presidential nominee have noticed that his hearing and vision are selective when it comes to such displays, as he proved Thursday at one stop in <LOCATION> Arkansas </LOCATION>, home of the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arkansas </ORGANIZATION>' Razorback Hogs. When <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> walked to his car for the next appearance, a voice from the crowd loudly shouted `` Chicken Hawk!'' <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>, apparently not hearing the taunt correctly, smiled and gave a thumbs-up signal. `` Go Hogs!'' <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> shouted back.
