<TEXT>
 There are campaign songs and campaign songs, but the one that was piped over the public address system on Sen. <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>'s plane recently was loudly booed by an unappreciative audience of reporters. Sung by <PERSON> Sylvia </PERSON> <PERSON> Johns </PERSON>, the song, entitled `` <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s Song,'' had an unmemorable tune and this sampling of lyrics: `` From <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> to the White House Is where <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> is gon na be Loyal to his country for American unity We the people of the <LOCATION> USA </LOCATION> Need a strong leader in the White House today It's <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> He's everybody's All American.'' The song was recorded in <LOCATION> Baton </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Rouge </LOCATION>, and complimentary 45 rpm copies were distributed to the press, courtesy of <ORGANIZATION> Bengal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Chemical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which the record jacket notes is a manufacturer of <ORGANIZATION> Bengal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roach </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Spray </ORGANIZATION>.
