f work would provide the correct emphasis to express political demands ... as there are also those who believe that by using such methods they can acquire undue advantages,'' <PERSON> Grosz </PERSON> was quoted as saying. The strike coincided with labor unrest in <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>. Hundreds of Polish miners work in Hungarian shafts. But the official media did not say if any Poles were involved in the 20-hour stoppage at the <LOCATION> Komlo </LOCATION> mine. The mining industry in <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION> has been crippled for at least 10 years due to producion lags, financial problems and a growing labor shortage. <LOCATION> Hungary </LOCATION>'s official trade unions have been critical of recent economic policy, emphasizing that workers, retirees and the unemployed must be protected against inflation, already at 18 percent this year.
