Replacement</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALYERSVILLE, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A teen-ager who was named a high school cheerleader after a member of the squad died in an auto accident was dropped from the squad at the request of the dead girl's mother. The decision to remove <PERSON> Nikki </PERSON> <PERSON> Cheek </PERSON>, 14, from the junior varsity cheerleader squad has sparked controversy at <ORGANIZATION> Magoffin </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Christy </PERSON> <PERSON> Michelle </PERSON> <PERSON> Caudill </PERSON>, 14, a popular cheerleader, was killed in a car-truck collision May 27 along with her 16-year-old brother and another girl. <PERSON> Nikki </PERSON> was named to replace <PERSON> Christy </PERSON>, but on July 8, county Schools Superintendent <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> <PERSON> Whitaker </PERSON> removed her from the squad at the request of <PERSON> Christy </PERSON>'s mother, <PERSON> Carrie </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Caudill </PERSON>. Mrs. <PERSON> Caudill </PERSON> said <PERSON> Whitaker </PERSON> acted out of compassion for a mother whose only children had died. <PERSON> Christy </PERSON>'s spot on the squad, she said, should be left vacant in her memory. `` It was a bad situation, a no-win situation,'' <PERSON> Whitaker </PERSON> said today. `` It's hurting both families.'' `` I know it really put him on a spot,'' said Mrs. <PERSON> Caudill </PERSON>. `` God knows, I do n't want to hurt another kid, but I just think as hard as my daughter worked at it, and she's gone; in memory of her, they ought to hold it open.'' But <PERSON> Nikki </PERSON>'s mother and father, <PERSON> Patty </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Cheek </PERSON>, criticized the action. In a letter to the <LOCATION> Salyersville </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Independent </LOCATION>, they expressed `` deepest sympathy'' for Mrs. <PERSON> Caudill </PERSON> but said she and <PERSON> Whitaker </PERSON> had decided `` to hurt another innocent child.'' <PERSON> Nikki </PERSON> received threatening phone calls after being named to replace <PERSON> Christy </PERSON> `` saying she should n't be taking the place of a girl that was killed in the accident,'' the letter said. The letter also said <PERSON> Nikki </PERSON> attended six or seven practices before she was removed. Mrs. <PERSON> Caudill </PERSON> said she discussed the situation with Mrs. Cheek several weeks after <PERSON> Nikki </PERSON> was named a cheerleader. `` I told Mrs. Cheek that <PERSON> Nikki </PERSON> had other years she could be cheerleader,'' Mrs. <PERSON> Caudill </PERSON> said. `` <PERSON> Christy </PERSON> could not try out again.''
