odyguards were killed and 11 wounded. <ORGANIZATION> La </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Epoca </ORGANIZATION> quoted <PERSON> Manns </PERSON>, also a poet and author, as saying he had not decided whether to return and wanted `` security guarantees'' from the government. The Chilean <ORGANIZATION> Journalists </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> said 32 journalists are among the exiles affected. They include <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Miguel </PERSON> <PERSON> Varas </PERSON>, a communist who lives in <LOCATION> Moscow </LOCATION> and broadcasts a daily radio program, `` The Voice of <LOCATION> Chile </LOCATION>.''
