<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Critics of the <ORGANIZATION> Suzuki </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Samurai </ORGANIZATION> have failed to demonstrate the sport-utility vehicle has an excessive tendency to roll over, federal regulators have said in denying a recall petition. However, the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Highway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Traffic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> began proceedings Thursday to establish standards to protect drivers of all light-duty vehicles `` against unreasonable risk of rollover.''
