<HEAD>Continental Allowed to Use State Law in Crash Lawsuit Cases</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> won a major federal court victory when a judge ruled lawsuits from the 1987 crash of a <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> jetliner at <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION> will be tried under <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION> law. The decision, reached Thursday, would allow a maximum award of $ 45,000 in physical damages to relatives of crash victims who have no dependants. The decision could save the carrier millions of dollars because <LOCATION> Colorado </LOCATION> law is considered the most restrictive in the nation in assessing damages. Lawyers for crash victims had sought trial under a more liberal <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> law. <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> Judge <PERSON> Sherman </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Finesilver </PERSON> has not yet decided what law will govern the award of punitive damages _ those damages awarded if the airline or others are found negligent. A hearing on that issue is set for Oct. 18. The <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> is scheduled to release its ruling on the cause of the crash at a hearing in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION> on Sept. 27. <ORGANIZATION> Continental </ORGANIZATION> Flight 1713 crashed on takeoff Nov. 15, 1987, killing 28 passengers and crew. Dozens of suits have been filed against the airline and its parent, <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Finesilver </PERSON> also on Thursday set a Dec. 5 trial date for crash lawsuits He ruled that only one of the suits will be tried then as a way to save time and money. The outcome of that suit, which will be selected as the most representative of the lot, will de